tps:\/\/www.superiorconstruction.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/SC-Quote-MakeALife-1000x343.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1055px) 100vw, 1055px\" \/><\/p>\n<div style=\"font-size: 20px; margin-top: 30px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These words drove company decision making generations ago, and they continue to guide our operations today. <\/span><\/div>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Superior Construction\u2019s entrepreneurial spirit, quality construction, and pursuit of complex projects began in the 1920s. Established in Gary, Indiana, the company foundation has always been in building the infrastructure of America. Schools, post offices, and libraries are some of the first projects Superior Construction completed, helping shape the America we know today. As the company grows, so too do the types of work we perform. We now take on large, complex structures in transportation, industrial, and a variety of necessary American infrastructure, delivering quality work safely and honestly nationwide.<\/span> <\/p>\n<h2>Safety always comes first<\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As a family-owned company, the monuments we construct are always secondary to a safe working culture. Superior Construction is known as an industry leader in progressive safety programs, exemplified by having one of the best safety records in the industry. We place high value on providing a safe work environment and continual training for our employees, and we maintain and build these standards by leveraging our Health, Safety, and Environmental group; implementing best-in-class technology solutions; and providing high-quality training. We invest in safety because we care that each of our employees goes home healthy at the end of each day.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Each Superior Construction employee is held accountable, and our Health, Safety, and Environment (HSE) professionals work side-by-side with our operations professionals. This helps ensure we\u2019re implementing current technologies and HSE protocols on every job and task we are involved in. Our HSE program begins with each employee, from the top down \u2014 empowering them to make safe decisions and speak up as necessary. Keeping safety at the forefront protects our employees while ensuring the safety of the communities we serve.<\/span> <\/p>\n<h2>About our Company<\/h2>\n<p>Superior Construction is an American family-owned infrastructure contractor dedicated to providing our clients with innovative solutions from industry experts and leaders. First established in 1923 as the J Largura Company, the now fourth-generation family business evolved into Superior Construction by 1938 and has been delivering #SuperiorResults ever since. Throughout its history, the company\u2019s foundation has always been building the infrastructure of America, successfully delivering heavy civil projects across numerous delivery methods, with a specialty in design-build. We provide unique design solutions, forward-thinking technology, and a safe work environment to create the most value for clients, employees and the community. We are Superior Construction! <\/p>\n<h2>How we give back<\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We don\u2019t just help improve the infrastructure of our country by building essential construction projects \u2014 we also invest in the communities we call home.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As citizens and active neighbors in these communities, this is our responsibility. Each Superior Construction regional office identifies community needs and gets involved at a local level. Through volunteer work, civic commitments, and encouraging local hiring, we strive to be community builders rather than just general contractors.<\/span> <\/p>\n<h2>Our leadership team<\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is a company built on quality, innovation, and hard work<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> \u2014 <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">guiding principles have been the cornerstone for the Largura family since its inception. Superior Construction is a fourth-generation, family\u2013owned business led by CEO Nick Largura. The Largura family continues to provide leadership and strategy, and Nick, supported by industry leaders and experts, holds the company to the high standards while leading with integrity, vision, and commitment.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/superiorconstr.wpengine.com\/who-we-are\/leadership\" class=\"btn\" target=\"_self\">Meet Our Leaders<\/a> <\/p>\n<h2>CULTURE<\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At Superior Construction, our employees are an extension of and embody our company values. In addition to working on projects with some of the best talent in the industry, our employees hold each other accountable and constantly challenge each other to do better. Our strong sense of loyalty is reciprocated by our employees, as seen through an average length of service of more than 10 years.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><strong>Why Superior Construction?<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Safety<\/li>\n<li>Opportunity<\/li>\n<li>Advancement opportunities<\/li>\n<li>Work \/ life integration<\/li>\n<li>Accountability<\/li>\n<li>Respect<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>These words drove company decision making generations ago, and they continue to guide our operations today. Superior Construction\u2019s entrepreneurial spirit, quality construction, and pursuit of complex projects began in the 1920s. Established in Gary, Indiana, the company foundation has always been in building the infrastructure of America. Schools, post offices, and libraries are some of [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":3,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"inline_featured_image":false,"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_ac